 3.  to implement multi-factor authentication by making use of a conditional access policy
     conditional access policy must be applied or assigned to Users and Groups.
     The conditional access policy must be applied when users access the Azure portal, which is a cloud app. That is: Microsoft Azure Management
     Access control must require multi-factor authentication when granting access

     simplified version
     You want all users in the "IT Team" group to use MFA when they log into the Azure portal.
     Create a Conditional Access Policy targeting that group, set Microsoft Azure Management as the cloud app,
      and configure the access control to enforce MFA.

4 .  connect to the SQL database via Microsoft SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS)
     also developers should use their on-premises Active Directory account for authentication
 ans -->    Active Directory integrated authentication.
 example - ff a developer in your company needs to connect to the SQL database using their corporate credentials,
 they can select "Active Directory - Integrated" in SSMS and authenticate without entering separate credentials.

 5. allow recovery of an accidental deletion of the key vault or key vault objects for 90 days after deletion
     az keyvault update --enable-soft-delete true --enable-purge-protection true

     az keyvault update --enable-soft-delete true --enable-purge-protection true

Soft delete: Allows you to recover a deleted key vault or key vault objects within 90 days.
Purge protection: Ensures that even after deletion, the key vault or its objects cannot be permanently deleted (purged) before the retention period (90 days).


     Purge protection is an optional Key Vault behavior and is not enabled by default
     Purge protection can only be enabled once soft-delete is enabled.
     When purge protection is on, a vault or an object in the deleted state cannot be purged until the retention period has passed.
     Soft-deleted vaults and objects can still be recovered, ensuring that the retention policy will be followed.
     default retention period is 90 days, once saved it cannot be changed

