 7. what is a san ,, can it replace cdn
   A Storage Area Network (SAN) is a dedicated network that provides access to consolidated, block-level data storage.
    It is used to increase the availability of data and improve the performance of applications that require access to shared data.
    However, SANs do not provide features to ensure high availability of web applications, nor do they provide a
    mechanism to store data in the geographic location nearest to the user.

    it cannot replace a cdn

    A company uses a SAN to connect multiple servers to a central storage system.
    This allows the servers to access shared data quickly, improving the performance of their internal databases and applications.

    A video streaming service uses a CDN to store copies of videos in data centers around the world.
    When a user plays a video, the CDN delivers it from the server closest to the user's location, reducing load times and improving playback quality.
    Global content distribution for faster access to users worldwide

   8.Activity Log Signal Type: Monitors operations on resources, useful for tracking resource management events but not for performance metrics.
     Application Log Signal Type: Captures logs generated by applications, allowing for alerting based on specific log entries, but not focused on performance counters.
     Metric Signal Type: Measures performance data over time, ideal for tracking performance counters and enabling alerts based on thresholds.
     Audit Log Signal Type: Tracks changes to resources for compliance and governance, but not intended for performance metrics.

     Signal Type	   Scenario	                                           Key Difference	Performance Monitoring
     Activity Log	   Track resource creation/deletion in Azure.	       Focuses on resource management events, not application performance.	Not for performance metrics.
     Application Log   Monitor specific application errors or events.	   Captures logs generated by applications, not focused on performance.	Not for performance counters.
     Metric	           Monitor CPU usage of a virtual machine over time.   Measures performance data (e.g., CPU, memory) and allows threshold-based alerts.	Ideal for performance monitoring.
     Audit Log	       Track    resource access or changes for governance.	 Tracks changes for compliance and auditing, not for performance.	Not for performance metrics.


