 11. You create the index in Azure Search. You now need to use the Azure Search .NET SDK to import the relevant data into the Azure Search service.
    what 3 steps are needed to be taken

     1. create an index search client  Create a Search Index Client:
     var serviceClient = new SearchServiceClient("YourSearchServiceName", new SearchCredentials("YourAdminKey"));
     var indexClient = serviceClient.Indexes.GetClient("YourIndexName");
     2. Create the indexBatch with the documents Create Documents
     var documents = new List<Document>
     3. opulate the newly-created index  Upload Documents to Azure Search:
      IndexBatch.Upload(documents);


13. Containers in the same group share the same lifecycle, resources, network, and volumes.
 Azure Container Group, part of Azure Container Instances

 eg - If you deploy a web app and a logging service in the same container group,
 they can communicate through localhost and share storage volumes for logging purposes,
 and they will be managed as a single unit in terms of lifecycle.